        "# Satellite Telemetry Anomaly Detection Benchmark Using the Hybrid Satellite Telemetry Dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "## Introduction\n",
        "I use this notebook to reproduce a compact version of the paper pipeline. I keep the same dataset assumptions, fault taxonomy, and per-satellite generalization split.\n"
      ],
      "id": "88223888"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "If Kaggle cell copy introduces quote issues, I also provide a copy-safe script in this repository: `kaggle/benchmark_notebook.py`.\n"
      ],
      "id": "5cafbe31"
        "I built this notebook to demonstrate a reproducible benchmark workflow for my Hybrid Satellite Telemetry dataset. Most classic telemetry benchmarks provide binary anomaly labels only, but this dataset provides fault-type labels so I can evaluate which failure modes are detectable by different model classes.\n",
        "\n",
        "I mirror the paper workflow at a compact scale: telemetry loading, recurrence plot encoding, baseline models, CNN recurrence-plot autoencoder, per-fault metrics, and hardware-noise comparison.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_fscore_support, classification_report\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_fscore_support, classification_report\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models\n",
        "\n",
        "np.random.seed(42)\n",
        "tf.random.set_seed(42)\n"
      ],
      "id": "261c7daf"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
